    "summary": "Christina is a passionate young professional devoting her life to reducing the disparities among different social groups and promoting sustainable development. She is an Economist and Project manager with experience in policy analysis. Her thematic focus is on the fields of social inclusion and sustainable transition. Her expertise covers advocacy, evidence-based solutions approach, project implementation and evaluation, policy impact assessment (Theory of Change), and cost-benefit analysis. \n\nChristina has contributed to the Public and Civil Society sector on programs empowering communities to take action on inequalities and environmental pollution (\u2018\u2019Talk Talk\u2019\u2019, Goethe Institute), tackling discrimination (\u2018\u2019MURAL\u2019\u2019, European Commission under the Rights, Equality and Citizenship Programme), and promoting quality education, active citizenship and climate change mitigation (\u2018\u2019Active Citizens\u2019\u2019, British Council). Her earlier role was as a Research Assistant at the International Center on Research on the Environment and Economy and she had the chance to work with prestigious researchers on projects funded by the European Commission focusing on micro- and macroeconomic management of the energy sector, governance, and institutional analysis.\n\nShe believes in youth leadership, holistic approaches, and sustainable innovative solutions against global societal challenges. From 2020 until 2022 she was appointed as Project Lead of the Youth Membership programme at the UN SDSN. As the Project Lead, she was leading a community of +778 youth-led and youth-focused organizations (non-profit and social enterprises) from all over the world helping them to accelerate their impact. From 2016 to 2018, Christina executed as the Network Coordinator of Greece of SDSN Youth, educating young people on the localization of the Agenda 2030. \n\nShe holds a master's degree in Policy Economics from Erasmus School of Economics and a bachelor's degree from Athens University of Economics and Business in the department of International and European Economic studies. \n\n\nSPECIALITIES\nEconomics focusing on social impact, policy analysis & community empowerment.\n\nRESEARCH INTERESTS\n Policy evaluation, Feminist-Economics, Environmental Economics, Sustainable Blue Economy, Sustainable Transition.",
